# General Code Rules

## Basic Rules

- Repository always returns `Result<T>`
- No UseCases — Executor calls Repository directly
- No comments in code
- NPE-safety: forbid `!!`, `list.first()`, `list.last()`
- Use `firstOrNull()`, `getOrNull()`, `orEmpty()`
- Always override `onCleared()` in ViewModel and call `store.dispose()`

## Access Modifiers

Everything is as closed as possible by default:

| Scope                          | Modifier         | Note                                                      |
|-------------------------------|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|
| Class / interface in impl      | `internal`       | Not visible outside the module                            |
| Class / interface in api       | `public`         | Only when needed by other modules (Store, ViewModel)      |
| Class fields                   | `private`        | Unless part of the contract                               |
| Functions                      | `private`        | Helper functions inside a class                           |
| Top-level                      | `internal`       | By default                                                |

| Entity                    | Modifier                            | Example                                        |
|---------------------------|-------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Store interface           | `public`                            | `interface UserListStore`                      |
| Repository interface      | `internal`                          | `internal interface UserListRepository`        |
| Repository impl           | `internal`                          | `internal class UserListRepositoryImpl`        |
| ApiClient interface       | `internal`                          | `internal interface UserListApiClient`         |
| ApiClient impl            | `internal`                          | `internal class UserListApiClientImpl`         |
| Mapper interface          | `internal`                          | `internal interface UserItemMapper`            |
| Mapper impl               | `internal`                          | `internal class UserItemMapperImpl`            |
| Remote DTO                | `internal`                          | `internal data class RemoteUser`               |
| Executor                  | `internal`                          | `internal class UserListExecutor`              |
| Reducer                   | `internal`                          | `internal class UserListReducer`               |
| StoreFactory              | `internal`                          | `internal class UserListStoreFactory`          |
| Message (sealed)          | `internal` (inside StoreFactory)    | `internal sealed interface Message`            |
| ViewModel                 | `public`, constructor `internal`    | `class UserListViewModel internal constructor` |
| UiState / UiLabel         | `public`                            | `data class UiUserListState`                   |

**Fields and properties:**
- All constructor dependencies — `private val`
- `MutableStateFlow` and other mutable fields — `private`
- Only immutable `StateFlow`/`Flow` are public for UI subscription

**Functions:**
- Helpers inside a class — `private`
- `override` functions inherit interface visibility
- Mapping extension functions inside a mapper — `private`

## Class Member Ordering

```kotlin
class SomeClass {
    // 1. Properties (private, internal, public)
    // 2. Init blocks
    // 3. Override methods
    // 4. Public methods
    // 5. Internal methods
    // 6. Private methods
    // 7. Companion object — ALWAYS last

    private companion object {
        const val SOME_CONST = 20
    }
}
```

**Companion object is always at the end of the class** — no exceptions.
